{
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "text": "%md\n# Bristol City Council land and building assets challenge\n## Unit 2 problem definition and suggested solutions (Zeppelin)\n\nThis note runs on Apache Zeppelin against Spark through Livy. Each Python paragraph starts with `%livy2.pyspark` so the cluster interpreter is selected. The shared `spark` session is already available: you load the Bristol CSV from `/HdiSamples/BristolCityCouncilLandAndBuildingAssets-2024.csv`, inspect `df`, then answer the questions. Each question uses the **DataFrame API** first and the same logic with **`spark.sql`** (and sometimes the `%livy2.sql` interpreter where Zeppelin charts help).",
      "user": "anonymous",
      "progress": 0,
      "config": {
        "tableHide": false,
        "editorSetting": {
          "language": "markdown",
          "editOnDblClick": true,
