      "dateCreated": "2025-10-28T14:18:59+0000",
      "status": "READY",
      "focus": true
    },
    {
      "text": "%md\n### Approach A: DataFrame API, then matplotlib\n\nSummarise in Spark, `toPandas()` for a small result set, then draw bars. `matplotlib` uses the `Agg` backend so it works in headless cluster contexts.",
      "user": "anonymous",
      "progress": 0,
      "config": {
        "tableHide": false,
        "editorSetting": {
          "language": "markdown",
          "editOnDblClick": true,
          "completionKey": "TAB",
          "completionSupport": false
        },
        "colWidth": 12,
        "editorMode": "ace/mode/markdown",
        "fontSize": 9,
        "editorHide": true,
        "results": {},
        "enabled": true
